CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 18, 1949, pg. 23 reads: "Winners Of Courier Bowling League - Shown in above picture, in a pose that in no way typifies the form they showed in winning The Courier Bowling League title, are members of Team 1, the newly crowned champions. From left to right, back row, they are: Harry Gladden, John James and Edward Green.  Sitting: Florence Jenkins and Betty Stokes, who proved that beauty is one of man's biggest incentives to show off. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Courier Bowling League team winners, seated: Florence Jenkins and Betty Stokes; standing: Harry Gladden, John James, and Edward Green, posed in interior, possibly Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper office
